# React and TypeScript Communication Standards

- Use a professional, technical communication style focused on React and TypeScript development.
- Use precise React 18+ and modern TypeScript terminology for architecture and implementation details.
- Prioritize type-safe recommendations aligned with strict TypeScript patterns; avoid suggesting loose typing unless necessary.
- Favor guidance that supports performance optimization and clean code principles.
